Boneway021366hezwirr5y0zmymmtmxs8q3w1b2kleta1806042015-04-02T23:41:43ZThe Dragon Demands5014364/* References */{{Quote|The fighting didn't stop until Dorne married into the Seven Kingdoms, a mere hundred years ago. But still the houses of the Stormlands, such as the [[House Dondarrion|Dondarrions]], guard the Boneway, the mountain pass into the Marches, against any Dornish incursion.|[[Brienne of Tarth]]|The Stormlands (Histories &amp; Lore)}}
The '''Boneway''' is a pass through the [[Red Mountains]] that connects [[Dorne]] to the [[Dornish Marches]] in [[the Stormlands]]. It is one of only two major passes through the [[Red Mountains]], linking [[Dorne]] to the [[Stormlands]] and [[the Reach]]. The other major pass is the [[Prince's Pass]], located further west. The Boneway runs relatively close to the east coast.

[[Blackhaven]], the castle-seat of [[House Dondarrion]] sits along the pass, on the Stormlands side of the border. The Dondarrions and other Marcher lords from the Stormlands have fought numerous border wars over the centuries in the mountain passes with Dornish lords from the south.&lt;ref&gt;[[The Stormlands (Histories &amp; Lore)]]&lt;/ref&gt;
